-- South Africa Beats Pakistan by Four Wickets to Ensure Series Win
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-02-17T16:28:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-17/south-africa-beats-pakistan-by-four-wickets-to-ensure-series-win.html
South Africa defeated Pakistan by
four wickets in the second cricket Test to take a decisive 2-0
lead in a three-game series.  Pakistan scored 338 in its first innings, Younis Khan and
Asad Shafiq both scoring 111 at Cape Town. The visitors slumped
to 169 all out in the second innings, Vernon Philander taking 4-
40 and  Dale Steyn  3-38.  South Africa got 326 in its first innings and 182-6 in its
second,  Hashim Amla  making 58, to wrap up victory on the fourth
day.  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 